Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each
half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 1cm pieces. Chop
each @cooked beetroot{250%g} into 6 segments. Trim the @tri-coloured Chantenay
carrots{150%g}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel).

Pop the carrots and beetroot on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle
with @oil{} and @honey{15%g}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to
coat, then spread out on the tray in a single layer.

Pop the aubergine on a separate baking tray, drizzle with @oil{} and
@miso paste{15%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat well and
spread out in a single layer. Bake the beetroot and carrots on the top shelf
and the aubergine on the middle shelf until both trays of veg are tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

> Use more baking trays if necessary, you want the veg nicely spread out.

Pour the @water{} for the bulgur wheat (see ingredients for amount) into a
#saucepan with the @vegetable stock powder{1} and bring to the boil. Stir in
the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for
~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side
for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Pick the @mint{1}(roughly chopped) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop
(discard the stalks). Quarter the @pomegranate{1/2}. Holding the pomegranate
pieces over a #bowl of water, scoop out the seeds into the bowl of water.
Scoop out the seeds and set aside. Discard the white pith.

> Use a fork to do this, it helps to release the seeds.

Once the bulgur is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork. Stir in three quarters
of the mint (keeping a little for serving), and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} to taste.

Divide the bulgur among #plates and top with the honeyed carrot and beetroot
as well as the miso aubergine. Drizzle with @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}
and finish off with pomegranate seeds and the remaining mint leaves. Enjoy!